      "id": 11,
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "# Retry Policy Monitoring\n\n**Status**: This dashboard shows metrics from the retry-job service, which runs every 15 minutes.\n\n**Expected Behavior**: \n- If you see \"No Data\", the retry-job may not have run yet, or there are no stuck/failed documents.\n- Metrics appear after the first successful retry-job execution.\n- Zero values are **normal** when the pipeline is healthy and processing without issues.\n\n**Troubleshooting**: \n1. Check if retry-job is running: `docker compose ps retry-job`\n2. View retry-job logs: `docker compose logs retry-job`\n3. Manually trigger: `docker compose run --rm retry-job python /app/scripts/retry_stuck_documents.py --once`\n\n**Documentation**: See [RETRY_POLICY.md](https://github.com/Alan-Jowett/CoPilot-For-Consensus/blob/main/documents/RETRY_POLICY.md)"
      },
      "title": "Dashboard Information"
    },
